          XXXXmmmmFFFFoooonnnnttttLLLLiiiisssstttt is the data type for a font list.  Font lists
          contain information corresponding to one or more fonts.
          Each element of the font list includes a font and a
          corresponding character set.  When a compound string is
          displayed, the character sets in the compound string are
          matched with the character sets in the font list, and the
          corresponding fonts in the font list are used to display the
          string.  If the character set in a compound string segment
          does not match any character set in the font list, the first
          font in the font list is used to display that segment.  The
          font list interface consists of the routines listed under
          "Related Information."

          Font lists are specified in resource files using the
          following syntax:

          _r_e_s_o_u_r_c_e__s_p_e_c :::: _f_o_n_t__n_a_m_e [ ==== _c_h_a_r_s_e_t ] [ ,,,, _f_o_n_t__n_a_m_e [ ====
          _c_h_a_r_s_e_t ] ]+

          The resource value string consists of one or more font list
          elements separated by commas.  Each font list element is a
          font name and an optional character set.  If a character set
          is specified for a font list element, it follows the font
          name and is separated from the font name by ====.  If no
          character set is specified, the character set is derived
          from the current language environment.


